    <!-- What it is -->
    <section class="section fade-up fade-up-5">
        <h2>An open knowledge layer</h2>
        <p>Every AI you use stores your context as one flat text file. Whatever you said yesterday, your AI doesn't really remember. And to give it context, you have to talk to it&mdash;there's no way to just <em>think</em> and have it become context.</p>
        <p>Parachute is a different shape: a personal knowledge graph organized around <strong>notes, tags, and links</strong>, accessible to any AI via <a href="https://modelcontextprotocol.io" target="_blank">MCP</a>&mdash;the open standard for connecting AI to tools. You spin up a vault, give any AI a link, and that's the whole setup. Whatever AI you already use&mdash;Claude, ChatGPT, Gemini&mdash;Parachute makes it smarter.</p>
    </section>

    <!-- Two pieces -->
    <section class="section fade-up fade-up-6">
        <h2>Two pieces</h2>

        <div class="products paths">
            <div class="product">
                <p class="path-label">Capture</p>
                <h3>Parachute Daily</h3>
                <p>Voice-first journal. Talk or type, on phone, web, or pendant. Three tabs&mdash;Reader, Capture, Vault&mdash;so you can think out loud, process what you've read, and find anything later. Local on-device transcription, offline-first, syncs to your vault when you're connected.</p>
                <p><a href="https://github.com/ParachuteComputer/parachute-daily" target="_blank">github.com/ParachuteComputer/parachute-daily &rarr;</a></p>
            </div>

            <div class="product">
                <p class="path-label">Store</p>
                <h3>Parachute Vault</h3>
                <p>A self-hosted knowledge graph with notes, tags, links, full-text and semantic search&mdash;exposed over MCP. One command sets up a daemon, configures Claude Code, and gives any AI agent a personal vault. Imports and exports Obsidian. Your data lives in SQLite, on your machine.</p>
                <p><a href="https://github.com/ParachuteComputer/parachute-vault" target="_blank">github.com/ParachuteComputer/parachute-vault &rarr;</a></p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <p>Daily writes into the Vault. The Vault speaks MCP. Any AI you use reads from the same memory. No migration, no export step&mdash;the same notes, the same graph, all the way through.</p>
    </section>

