    <!-- Principles -->
    <section class="section">
        <h2>Principles</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Voice-first.</strong> Talking is often more natural than typing. We meet people where their thinking actually happens&mdash;on walks, in the car, away from the desk.</li>
            <li><strong>Local-first.</strong> Your data lives on your machine in a SQLite database. If we disappeared tomorrow, your data would still be there&mdash;portable, exportable, entirely yours.</li>
            <li><strong>Open standard.</strong> Built on MCP. Works with whatever AI you already use, and whatever you use next. We're not tied to a single model.</li>
            <li><strong>Open source as trust.</strong> The only way to deserve trust with personal thinking is transparency. You can read every line of code that touches your notes.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- Get Started -->
    <section class="section">
        <h2>Get started</h2>
        <p>Parachute is in active development. Both repos are open source.</p>
        <div class="product">
            <h3>Run a vault</h3>
            <div class="code-inline">
                <code>git clone https://github.com/ParachuteComputer/parachute-vault &amp;&amp; cd parachute-vault &amp;&amp; bun install &amp;&amp; bun src/cli.ts vault init</code>
            </div>
            <p>Requires <a href="https://bun.sh" target="_blank">Bun</a>. <code>vault init</code> walks you through setup, starts a background daemon on port 1940, and configures Claude Code's MCP automatically. From there, point Parachute Daily at it&mdash;or just talk to your favorite AI and watch it reach into your vault.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

